section_title: Emergency provision to have permanent effect.
section_text: 6 In the  Government and other Stocks (Emergency Provisions) Act 1939, section one (which makes provision for rendering inscribed stock transferable by instrument in writing) shall have permanent effect . . .
7 Any expenses incurred by any government department which are attributable to the provisions of this Act shall be defrayed out of moneys provided by Parliament.

10 1 This Act may be cited as the Emergency Laws (Repeal) Act 1959. 2 The provisions of this Act, other than sections . . .   six therefore and this section, shall continue in force only until the expiration of the thirty-first day of December, nineteen hundred and sixty-four, and shall then expire; and  sections sixteen (1) and seventeen (2)(a) of the  Interpretation Act 1978 , shall apply upon the expiration of those provisions as if those provisions had then been repealed. 3 . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .
